    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-02-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="49"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kimberly</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in Central
                                America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-02-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received February
                        20).</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 246.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 243, of January 31, I have
                    the honor to report that to-day Señor Prado, acting minister of foreign
                    relations, in Señor Don F. Anguiano’s absence, called at this legation, and,
                    calling my attention to the instructions to Capt. Johnston, of Pacific Mail
                    steamship <hi rend="italic">City of New York</hi>, sent to him from me, asked
                    that the word “expiation “be stricken out and the word “explanation”
                    substituted. After a polite discussion I refused to comply with his request,
                    stating that the word “expiation” conveyed the precise meaning and literal sense
                    intended by me, and that it could not be changed without authority from my
                    Government.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Samuel Kimberly</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad int</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
